Vihiga Senator George Khaniri has said the country is doing badly after debt increased to Sh3.7 trillion under the Jubilee government.Yesterday he faulted the government for &ldquo;excessive borrowing&rdquo;. The senator spoke at his home in Serem. Khaniri said increased borrowing is tantamount to mortgaging the country.He said, &ldquo;If this is allowed to proceed untamed, we will not have a country to talk about.&rdquo;Khaniri, a critic of the Jubilee government, said poverty levels will rise if Jubilee leaders are reelected.He said the government is &ldquo;rooted in graft&rdquo;.&ldquo;Our economy has been grounded and people are going hungry,&rdquo; Khaniri said.He urged NASA leaders to stick together to &ldquo;redeem&rdquo; the country.In October last year, Khaniri and Lugari MP Ayub Savula were left in the cold when their UDF party dissolved to join the Jubilee Party.Khaniri opted not to join JP.